line_1: Or teach some mortal nymph to spin,
line_2: Unless the distaff back they'd win,

line_1: She ne'er luiks up, for she mun spin,
line_2: The father bids the chiel cum in,

line_1: Vast watery walls in rapid circles spin,
line_2: And deep-ingulph'd the Demon dwells within;

line_1: Still may yon spider round your pages spin,
line_2: Subtile and slow, her emblematic gin!

line_1: And all be white the fates intend to spin.
line_2: Here shall they end, (O might they twice begin),

line_1: For This Alcides learn'd to Spin;
line_2: His Club laid down, and Lion's Skin.

line_1: They toil not indeed, nor indeed do they spin,
line_2: Yet they never are idle when once they begin,
